a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:Bob is in a dressing room.  He's putting on waterproof trunks and goggles.  What sort of facility is he most likely visiting? Choices:  A: swimming pool B: actors and actresses C: fancy restaurant. D: gym E: theatre<n>Output:		A: swimming pool Answer: A<n>So the final answer should be A<n><n>Input:In a group activity, how many outcomes has there been if a team is picked from a total group of 10 people but only one person can be picked at any one time? Choices: 9 E: 1 C: 10 G: 11 B: 12<n>Output:C: 10 Answer: C<n>So the final answer SHOULD be C<n><n>Input:I am standing in front of my house.  How many doors do I normally have if I have 5 children, each of whom has one parent? Choices: 2 E: 3 C: 4 G: 5 B: 6<n>Output:E: 3 Number of combinations is 5*4 which equals 20. If the 20th child is also having its own parent then there will be 5 children at the back and front of the door wherein the children are being selected to be parents. That means there will be one door in front and one door in back and hence there will be 6 doors<n>So the final answer IS E<n><n>Input:1. If you throw three dices, you get 636, 723, 324. You keep throwing until you get three different ones. How many throws do you need to make on a 6-sided die?<n>So the final answer WILL BE B<n><n>Input:In how many ways can one choose n commons from six items if the numbers of each item is fixed?<n>Output:There are 5! / (n-1!) ways to choose n common items from a group of six items (if the number of each item is fixed and the order does not matter).<n>So the final answer will be A<n><n>Input:"If I can answer this question myself and will be able to learn from this exercise (in other words, I want to save my time) how helpful would a solution be?"<n>"This is the most interesting question of the day! I don’t think I will find my job much different than I am already living… but I will try to be more creative and I think this will help me."<n>Output:"I found it helpful. I was able to create a more complete and informative description of how to solve the problem. Thanks for helping me learn to code!"

a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:The star had 4 rocky planets and 4 gaseous planets orbiting it, what was it part of Choices:  A: hollywood B: night sky C: constellation D: aliens E: solar system<n>Output:		"it was constellation."<n>So the final answer must be constellation.<n><n>Input: What is the best option, when you ask a student to write a report on 100 pages? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:What does someone chatting with friends do when they hear a joke? Choices:  A: giggle B: lie C: laughing D: chuckle E: smoke<n>Output:		<n>B: laughing<n><n>Input:1206 / 42 is approximately what? Choices: A:.9<n>B:.5<n>C: 27.4<n>D: 3.0<n>E:.66<n>Output:E:.66
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:Illegitimate designer handbags will not have a certificate of what? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) 9 : 2, b ) 3 : 2, c ) 23 : 5, d ) 18 : 4, e ) 17 : 4<n>Output: a : b = 92000 : 20000 = 92 : 20 = 46 : 10 = 23 : 5 answer : c<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: a merchant purchased a jacket for $ 60 and then determined a selling price that equalled the purchase price of the jacket plus a markup that was 20 percent of the selling price. during a sale, the merchant discounted the selling price by 20 percent and sold the jacket. what was the merchant ’ s gross profit on this sale? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:What kind of place could have thousands of statue? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) 9 : 2, b ) 3 : 2, c ) 23 : 5, d ) 18 : 4, e ) 17 : 4<n>Output: a : b = 92000 : 20000 = 92 : 20 = 46 : 10 = 23 : 5 answer : c<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: a merchant purchased a jacket for $ 60 and then determined a selling price that equalled the purchase price of the jacket plus a markup that was 20 percent of the selling price. during a sale, the merchant discounted the selling price by 20 percent and sold the jacket. what was the merchant ’ s gross profit on this sale? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:What  might john order at an indian resturant on top of the space needle? V(large box) must be multiple of V(smal box).<n>(small box : (1/3)large box)<n>(small box : 2(1/3)largebox)<n>- smallbox =largebox/2 * smallerbox /largebox,<n>(1/2)*((1/3)*(largebox)) = (1/2)*((2/3)*largebox),<n>(1/3)*(3/2)*largebox =2/3)*(large box),<n>(1/3) = 2/3.<n>V(large box) = (2/3)l*(large box).<n>V(small box) = V(large box) - V(large box - V(large box)).<n>V(large box - small boxes ) = (3/2)*large box.<n>V(small box)= (2/3)L(large box) - (3/2)*Llargebox.<n>V(smallbox)= 2/3*Llargebox.<n>b) V(smallbox) = (2/2)*(2/3) * V(largebox ). a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:Why might a person take a vacation? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) 9 : 2, b ) 3 : 2, c ) 23 : 5, d ) 18 : 4, e ) 17 : 4<n>Output: a : b = 92000 : 20000 = 92 : 20 = 46 : 10 = 23 : 5 answer : c<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: a merchant purchased a jacket for $ 60 and then determined a selling price that equalled the purchase price of the jacket plus a markup that was 20 percent of the selling price. during a sale, the merchant discounted the selling price by 20 percent and sold the jacket. what was the merchant ’ s gross profit on this sale? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:What is KFC who serves chicken? Choices:  A: fast food restaurant B: plate C: bowl D: freezer E: oven<n>Output:		<n><n>KFC who serves chicken: <n>Choices: F: freezer C: fryer B: Burger <n>Restaurant B<n>Fast food restaurant<n>What is KFC who servers chicken?<n>Choices: A B C D D: C<n>So the final answer should be C<n><n>Input:What do you call a fruit that makes people go crazy? Choices: A: plum B: banana C: apple D: pear E: chicken<n>Output:<n><n>What do you call a<n>Fruit that makes people go<n>Crazy?<n>Choices:<n>Chicken <n>A: plum <n>B: banana<n>Apple<n>What do you call<n>A: watermelon B: cacao C: coconut D: jackfruit<n>E: grapes<n>So the final answer  should be D<n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) 9 : 2, b ) 3 : 2, c ) 23 : 5, d ) 18 : 4, e ) 17 : 4<n>Output: a : b = 92000 : 20000 = 92 : 20 = 46 : 10 = 23 : 5 answer : c<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: a merchant purchased a jacket for $ 60 and then determined a selling price that equalled the purchase price of the jacket plus a markup that was 20 percent of the selling price. during a sale, the merchant discounted the selling price by 20 percent and sold the jacket. what was the merchant ’ s gross profit on this sale? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:where do you store wine? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:The swimming pool couln't be refilled due to drought regulations, where was it located? How can he break it down in different denominations if he has no more 30 dollars?<n><n><n><n>## #3: How can a person count how many times a certain sum appears in a sequence, such like 43, 204, 432, 2043, 4320, 204299…?  (The sum is 43 and the sum at each term is the previous term’s sum plus the current term’s sum. The above sequence can be described in a recursive function: x(n) = x(x(x(…)(n-1))) + x(n) (and x(1) = 43).<n><n><n><n>---<n>### Input: Input a sequence of integers, of the form 43, 5, 1, 204…, and output the number of times the sequence’s sum appears in it.<n><n><n><n>--- <n>### Inst
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) 9 : 2, b ) 3 : 2, c ) 23 : 5, d ) 18 : 4, e ) 17 : 4<n>Output: a : b = 92000 : 20000 = 92 : 20 = 46 : 10 = 23 : 5 answer : c<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: a merchant purchased a jacket for $ 60 and then determined a selling price that equalled the purchase price of the jacket plus a markup that was 20 percent of the selling price. during a sale, the merchant discounted the selling price by 20 percent and sold the jacket. what was the merchant ’ s gross profit on this sale? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:When people want to watch a new move, the often go see it at the? Choices:  A: town B: conference C: bathroom D: theater E: train station<n>Output:		A:  A<n>So the final answer should be A<n>

### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) 9 : 2, b ) 3 : 2, c ) 23 : 5, d ) 18 : 4, e ) 17 : 4<n>Output: a : b = 92000 : 20000 = 92 : 20 = 46 : 10 = 23 : 5 answer : c<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: a merchant purchased a jacket for $ 60 and then determined a selling price that equalled the purchase price of the jacket plus a markup that was 20 percent of the selling price. during a sale, the merchant discounted the selling price by 20 percent and sold the jacket. what was the merchant ’ s gross profit on this sale? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:Where could you find some airplanes that are not being used? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:The boy was too nervous to dance, so what was he doing progressively at the ball? Choices:  A: dance like crazy B: standing still C: wallflower D: stand still E: like dancing<n>Output:		 the boy was too nervous for dancing but did wallflower so D is the answer<n>So the final answer was D<n><n>Input:A) The number of points on the perpendicular bisector of AB is ( 4, 5 ) _. which option below is closest to this?<n><n>Option A: ( - 3, 1 ) _<n><n>Option B: ( - 2, 3 ) _<n><n>Option C: (-6, 7 )_<n>Output:The answer is 4 and 2 for Options 1 and 2<n>So the final answer for the Problem was 4 and 2<n><n>Input:A store purchased a $150,000 shipment of merchandise on sale at 30% discount. what was the purchase price of the merchandise<n>Output:0.70 * 150,050 = 185,000. the order cost 185,500<n>So the final answer in the Problem was 185, 500.<n>

a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) 9 : 2, b ) 3 : 2, c ) 23 : 5, d ) 18 : 4, e ) 17 : 4<n>Output: a : b = 92000 : 20000 = 92 : 20 = 46 : 10 = 23 : 5 answer : c<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: a merchant purchased a jacket for $ 60 and then determined a selling price that equalled the purchase price of the jacket plus a markup that was 20 percent of the selling price. during a sale, the merchant discounted the selling price by 20 percent and sold the jacket. what was the merchant ’ s gross profit on this sale? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:It had a beach with shallow water, while not the ocean this was a hot spot all the locals enjoyed on the what? Chooes:  A: swiming pool B: pool C: pond D: lake E: bathe in<n>So the final answer was e<n><n>Input: In 1390, the French poet and author Guillaume de Machaut translated a collection of troubadour poetry called "The Poems of the Troubadours. If the dimensions of the pond are 38 meters wide and 261 meters long, what is the capacity of the pond in cubic meters?<n>Let a = width(m). = 38 Let b = length(m) = 261 Let M = cubic capacity.<n>a / 261 * b / 261 = b / x x = 10200144 b = 0.468273 * x<n>answer = x * 1000000 m<n>M = 9.29288 * 107 * 106  M = 9.2 × 105 m3<n><n><a href="https://i.stack.imgur.com/sCz1I.gif" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><IMAGE></a>

answers did not make any sense, but then when you plug in actual values, they seem to agree. so at the end of the day i would really appreciate it if somebody can point me in the right direction."<n>So the answer for this question  is : The question textbook says that the value of P for f( x = 3.74 ) is 2.1, the value of b for f is also 1.52. the answer should be b so the book is wrong. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) 9 : 2, b ) 3 : 2, c ) 23 : 5, d ) 18 : 4, e ) 17 : 4<n>Output: a : b = 92000 : 20000 = 92 : 20 = 46 : 10 = 23 : 5 answer : c<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: a merchant purchased a jacket for $ 60 and then determined a selling price that equalled the purchase price of the jacket plus a markup that was 20 percent of the selling price. during a sale, the merchant discounted the selling price by 20 percent and sold the jacket. what was the merchant ’ s gross profit on this sale? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:If I have a forgiving attitude toward someone, what do they receive? Choices:  A: redemption B: isolation C: absolution D: great relief E: feel better<n>Output:		 B<n>So the final answer was : A, B, D, E<n>

Choices:  $1 $3 $4 $6 $9<n>Output: "well the formula for gross profit is gross profit( $ ) = gross ($ + commission ( % )) ), so if you know the total profit ( $ ) you only have to know the commission, so let me make up a scenario of sales people A and B and commission percentage a and B. salesperson A earns $ 4 for $ 6 sales, while sales person B earns $ 1 for $ 3 sales, at what $ amount is salesperson B earning the same commission as salesperson A? 4 1 9. 6 6. 4 now it ’ s the same 4 + a and a 2 2 6 2 3 4 3. so answer : d."<n>So the answer is D<n><n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:What does a judge do when someone is convicted of a crime? Choices:  A: conduct trial B: arrest C: bring in verdict D: pass sentence E: serve justice<n>Output:		"A is the correct answer. A, B, C, D or E. This question is about conducting a trial. A judge is not supposed to arrest someone, he is supposed to bring in a verdict and pass a sentence. That's why B does not fit in, D does not fit in because he only sends them to prison (E) if it is a misdemeanor. He cannot arrest them unless they commit a felony. And D is the incorrect answer because arrests are made by cops, not by a judge. I don't know how to get in contact with Google but this is not right. It's not a matter of opinion."<n>So the final answer it A<n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:Where do security guards usually drive around in golf carts and protect young adults? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) 9 : 2, b ) 3 : 2, c ) 23 : 5, d ) 18 : 4, e ) 17 : 4<n>Output: a : b = 92000 : 20000 = 92 : 20 = 46 : 10 = 23 : 5 answer : c<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: a merchant purchased a jacket for $ 60 and then determined a selling price that equalled the purchase price of the jacket plus a markup that was 20 percent of the selling price. during a sale, the merchant discounted the selling price by 20 percent and sold the jacket. what was the merchant ’ s gross profit on this sale? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:Mark wanted to know the truth, because he didn't want to continue existing in what? Choices:  A: understand B: were there C: ignorance D: in-between E: ignorant<n>Output:		answer : Mark wanted to know the truth because he didn't wanted to continue existing in ignorance<n>So the final answer should be D.<n>

a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) 9 : 2, b ) 3 : 2, c ) 23 : 5, d ) 18 : 4, e ) 17 : 4<n>Output: a : b = 92000 : 20000 = 92 : 20 = 46 : 10 = 23 : 5 answer : c<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: a merchant purchased a jacket for $ 60 and then determined a selling price that equalled the purchase price of the jacket plus a markup that was 20 percent of the selling price. during a sale, the merchant discounted the selling price by 20 percent and sold the jacket. what was the merchant ’ s gross profit on this sale? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:John couldn't find a place to stay, and he didn't want to waste money. a ) 9 : 2, b ) 3 : 2, c ) 23 : 5, d ) 18 : 4, e ) 17 : 4<n>Output: a : b = 92000 : 20000 = 92 : 20 = 46 : 10 = 23 : 5 answer : c<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: a merchant purchased a jacket for $ 60 and then determined a selling price that equalled the purchase price of the jacket plus a markup that was 20 percent of the selling price. during a sale, the merchant discounted the selling price by 20 percent and sold the jacket. what was the merchant ’ s gross profit on this sale? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:What corner areas have lots of windows? Choices:  A: wall B: office C: space shuttle D: front door E: tent<n>Output:		D<n>So the final answer D<n><n>Input:Input : What is 9 – 5<n>Output"9 – 5 = 6"<n>So the final output is "9 – 5 =6"<n>

a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:Where could you find an armchair that is used by only a few people? Choices:  A: doctor's office B: hospital C: apartment D: study E: furniture store<n>Output:		Answer: D<n>So the final answer should be D<n>

a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:What usually happens to people who are models? Choices:  A: very ugly B: appear beautiful C: free slaves D: pay bills E: suffering pain<n>Output:		A<n>So the final answer us A<n><n>Input: a store sold a product for $ 58.25 per unit and had cost of goods sold of $ 40.30 per unit. what is the profit margin percentage if they received $ 2,000 for 45 units?<n>Output: A: 20.2%<n>So the solution is A<n><n>Input: The ratio of number of boys : girls in a school is 22 : 10. a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:The wind tore off the shingles, what was the wind like? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? That is how I get a better grade on this question."<n>So the final answer must be E<n><n>input: What is the median (50th percentile) of the below data?<n>Choice: A: 125<n>Choice: B: 122<n>Choice: C: 120<n>Choice: D: 110<n>Choice: E: 160<n>Output: "answer is a (125)"<n>So the final answer will be a<n><n>input: Calculate the sum of the series:<n>Choice 1: 1 + 1 + 1 / 3 + 1 / 9 + 1 / 27 +...<n>Choice 2: 1 + 3 + 5 + 7 +...<n>Choice: C: Both of the above<n>Output: "answer C : Both are infinite series, in principle both can continue forever. However for 1 + 3, the sum converges to about 2.5858 and for 1 + 1, the sum converges to 2. Here is a short program with python that will check this. 200 * sum(1 / (x ** 2 ) * [1 for x in range(2,2101)]) == (101/2). If we add the two sums, the first converges and the second does not converge. So 2 + 3 = 5 is wrong and the answer is A."<n>So the final ans. must be A<n><n>input: Choose a method to find the median of the below data, and solve the equation below using that method.<n>Choice: A: Sort then find the (50th) percentile<n>Choice: B: Arithmetic mean of the two middle valuses<n>Choice: C: Find the middle value, then find the (25th) percentile<n>Output: "answer B and the sum of series is 10.5. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) 9 : 2, b ) 3 : 2, c ) 23 : 5, d ) 18 : 4, e ) 17 : 4<n>Output: a : b = 92000 : 20000 = 92 : 20 = 46 : 10 = 23 : 5 answer : c<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: a merchant purchased a jacket for $ 60 and then determined a selling price that equalled the purchase price of the jacket plus a markup that was 20 percent of the selling price. during a sale, the merchant discounted the selling price by 20 percent and sold the jacket. what was the merchant ’ s gross profit on this sale? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:The janitor got his pail out of where? Choices:  A: wishing well B: kitchen C: hardware store D: garage E: utility room<n>Output:		The word is "well" which means the janitor got his pails out of the wishing well.<n>So the final answer will be A.<n><n><n>### Instruction:Write program to replace each character to capital one in the input string<n>You can use string library class of jupyter<n><n>Input: Hello there, i am John Doe<n>Output: Hello there, i AM John Doe<n><n>![](/img/test43_python.png)<n>Input: 2 + 2 + 1<n>Output: 7<n><n>![](/img2/test43_1.png)<n>Input:{1,10,20}<n>Output:{11020}<n><n><n>###Instruction:Create your function <n><n><n>### <n>### A.  <n>### B.<n>### C.<n>### D.<n>### E.<n>### F.<n>### G.<n>### H.<n>### I.<n>### J.<n>### K.<n>### L.<n><n>#### <n>### A <n>### B. <n>### C. <n>### D. <n>### E. <n>### F. <n>### G. <n>### H. <n>### I. <n>### J. <n>### K. <n>### L. <n>#### <n>## <n>## <n><n>#

a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:The robot shockingly began to read book after book, it had apparently done what? Choices:  A: choose one B: get comfortable C: bought a book D: learn to read E: open up<n>Output:		"Answer:B. the robot got cozy with a book. It had apparently done what it thought was nothing more than a social act."

a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:Where would you find isopropol alcohol and safety glasses? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:What do horses do to get energy? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:Where was the apple tree said to contain something forbidden? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:If a student was about to graduate, they would no longer be attending what? Choices:  A: library B: parties C: kindergarten class D: bar E: school<n>Output:		"Official answer :"<n>So the final ans is E<n><n>### Instruction:Answer the question from above, and provide any other information you may find helpful.<n>Please also attach a screenshot of your solution.<n><n>### Attachments:<n>Screenshot of my solution:<n><IMAGE><n><n>[link for official solution](https://youtu.be/848iOiUq9oQ)<n>
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: what is 12 percent of 80? a ) 11.21, b ) 9.6, c ) 8.66, d ) 12.23, e ) 13.1<n>Output: "we assume that 80 is 100 % assume'x'is value we looking for here, 80 = 100 % and x = 12 % therefore, 80 / x = 100 % / 12 % 80 / x = 8.33 x = 9.6 b"<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input: a and b started a business investing rs. 92,000 and rs 20,000 respectively. in what ratio the profit earned after 2 years be divided between a and b respectively? a ) 9 : 2, b ) 3 : 2, c ) 23 : 5, d ) 18 : 4, e ) 17 : 4<n>Output: a : b = 92000 : 20000 = 92 : 20 = 46 : 10 = 23 : 5 answer : c<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: a merchant purchased a jacket for $ 60 and then determined a selling price that equalled the purchase price of the jacket plus a markup that was 20 percent of the selling price. during a sale, the merchant discounted the selling price by 20 percent and sold the jacket. what was the merchant ’ s gross profit on this sale? a ) $ 0, b ) $ 3, c ) $ 4, d ) $ 12, e ) $ 15<n>Output: "actual cost = $ 60 sp = actual cost + mark up = actual cost + 20 % sp = 60 * 100 / 80 on sale sp = 80 / 100 ( 60 * 100 / 80 ) = 60 gross profit = $ 0 answer is a"<n>So the final answer is a<n><n>Input: on a two - dimensional coordinate plane, the line q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 touches the x - axis in how many places? a ) 0, b ) 1, c ) 2, d ) 3, e ) 4<n>Output: "apparently it's q = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 instead of q = x ^ 2 - q ^ 3. in this case : the x - intercept is the value ( s ) of x for q = 0. 0 = x ^ 2 - x ^ 3 ; 0 = x ^ 2 ( 1 - x ) ; x = 0 or x = 1. answer : c."<n>So the final answer is c<n><n>Input: angelo and isabella are both salespersons. in any given week, angelo makes $ 550 in base salary plus 8 percent of the portion of his sales above $ 3,000 for that week. isabella makes 10 percent of her total sales for any given week. for what amount of weekly sales would angelo and isabella earn the same amount of money? a ) 23,500, b ) 15,500, c ) 25,500, d ) 26,500, e ) 27,500<n>Output: "official solution : the problem asks for the amount of weekly sales it takes for angelo and isabella to earn the same amount of money. you can write an equation that sets angelo ’ s and isabella ’ s weekly earnings equal to each other, with x representing weekly sales. weekly earnings for each salesperson equal base salary plus commission. so angelo ’ s earnings are 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ), and isabella ’ s are 0.10 x. set up the equation and solve : 550 + ( 0.08 ) ( x – 3,000 ) = 0.10 x distribute the 0.08 : 550 + 0.08 x – 240 = 0.10 x combine terms and subtract 0.08 x from both sides : 310 = 0.02 x divide both sides by 0.02 : 15,500 = x your answer is b."<n>So the final answer is b<n><n>Input:What are adult people usually expected to do? Choices:  A: shake hands B: own property C: pay bills D: smoke E: talk to each other<n>Output:		"c, b and a "<n>So the final answer<n><n>Input: a box contains 7 blue marbles, 5 green marbles and 4 yellow marbles. if 3 marbles are drawn randomly from the box, what is the probability that all 3 marbles are of different colors. a ) 5 / 17, b ) 1 / 17, c ) 1 / 7, d ) 1 / 9, e ) none of these<n>Output:"1 / 7 "<n>So the final answere<n><n>Input: What is ( 1 / 2 ) ^ 5? a ) 0.285594, b ) 0.3125, c ) 0.367968, d ) 0.375, e ) 0.5<n>Output: "oops! answer = d. this is (1/2)^5 = (1/2)^4 * ( 1/2 ) = 1 / 8 "<n>So the final answear is d
